quoteLast: , either of surface or intensity. When mixed with its co-secondary colour, green, purple forms the tertiary _olive_; and, when compounded with the remaining secondary, orange, it constitutes in like manner the tertiary _russet_. Of the three secondary colours it is the coolest, as well as the nearest in relation to _black_ or shade; in which respect, and in never being a warm colour, it resembles blue.
